					<description><![CDATA[Construction and engineering works are progressing to plan at the copper-gold project in Brazil, with start-up expected in H2 2021.]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>Mineração Vale Verde and Appian Capital Advisory <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://appiancapitaladvisory.com/mvv-operational-update/" target="_blank">announced</a> on Tuesday the first blast at the Serrote copper-gold project in Alagoas, Brazil.</p>



<p>According to Appian, the pre-stripping program has now handled over one million tonnes of material. Construction and engineering works are progressing to plan, with start-up expected in H2 2021.</p>



<p>Based on definitive feasibility study (“DFS”), Serrote will require <a href="https://www.mining.com/appian-appoints-former-anglo-exec-to-lead-brazil-operations/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">$250 million in capital</a> for a conventional, low-strip open-pit operation targeted to produce 20,000 tonnes of copper equivalent per year over 14 years.</p>



<p>&#8220;Serrote continues to demonstrate robust economics with potential upside, and we are seeing strong interest from offtake and financing partners,&#8221;  said Paulo Castellari, CEO, Vale Verde &amp; Appian Brazil.</p>
